==English==

{{rank|lay|along|four|331|wish|gone|times|girl}}

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wyscan]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪʃ|-ɪʃ]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|wish|es}}

# to [[hope]] for a particular outcome
# to bestow a thought or gesture towards someone or something
#:''We '''wish''' you a Merry Christmas/We '''wish''' you...''

